article.description: Tyler Collet made a diving interception to thwart a late Southeastern Louisiana rally as Southern Utah held on for a 28-23 win on Saturday night.
article.headline: Collet's interception seals S. Utah's 28-23 win over SE La.
article.linkText: Collet's interception seals S. Utah's 28-23 win over SE La.
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Tyler Collet made a diving interception to thwart a late Southeastern Louisiana rally as Southern Utah held on for a 28-23 win on Saturday night. Southeastern Louisiana pulled to within five when Justin Alo hit Juwan Dickey on a 20-yard scoring strike with 3:33 left in the game. The Lions got the ball back with 1:12 remaining. With 54 seconds left, Josh Thornton tipped the pass and Collet scooped it out of the air to seal the win. Patrick Tyler led Southern Utah (1-1), throwing for 188 yards and three scores. Malik Brown rushed for 146 yards on 32 carries. Southeastern (0-2) held a 17-14 advantage at the break, but the Thunderbirds took the lead for good when Brady Measom hauled in a 10-yard scoring strike from Tyler. Tyler hit Sharp on a 16-yard scoring play with 9:27 left in the game to provide enough cushion for the win.
